Rating: 4
This recipe was a real hit for Thanksgiving and I will make it a tradition. After reviewing a similar recipe and user reviews, I revised by using 1/4 cup dried tart cherries with 1/4 cup of dried cranberries (instead of just the dried tart cherries). Also, I did not add the minced rosemary, opting instead to add three whole sprigs of fresh rosemary which I removed after simmering. Frozen cherries were hard to locate, finally found them at Ralph's & rinsed them so they were thawed enough to cut in half. Per one reviewers suggestion I used Trader Joe's dried cherries. This is an easy to make, outstanding cranberry sauce that your guests will love!!

Rating: 4
Absolutely delicious. I doubled the recipe and made this with a few more frozen dark cherries by using both bags and reduced the brown sugar by 1/2 cup. I also added two whole sprigs of rosemary near the end of cooking on the stove, which I simmered for about 30 minutes longer than the recipe specified. I refrigerated the sauce for a few days before serving it. Some friends stated that never really liked cranberry sauce but loved this. It would be a great jam or pie filling or even to serve with brie.

