Rating: 4
This recipe was AMAZING! It had so many flavors going on and it seemed very gourmet. I forgot to buy rosemary but it still turned out great. I added a teaspoon of butter at the very end in order to make it nice and glossy. Usually recipes for jam-like things call for this. It really made the sauce glisten. Also I simmered it for longer than 8 minutes to make it thicker. I waited until it cooled a bit and put half in the blender to puree it. I mixed the puree back into the remaining half and it really made the sauce the perfect consistency. Not too chunky but not too smooth.

